abstract: >-
  Management Research Notes is a portable, file-based academic knowledge
  base for management and business sustainability research. Each
  peer-reviewed article becomes one Markdown note with YAML frontmatter
  (trusted bibliographic metadata, a controlled-vocabulary topic taxonomy,
  three custom analytic fields — unit_of_analysis, level_of_theory,
  dependent_variable_family — and verbatim evidence anchors on every
  factual claim) and a human-readable distillation (research question,
  mechanism, theoretical contribution, practical implication, limitations,
  future research, APA citation). A small Python pipeline derives a SQLite
  index with FTS5, a CSV export, and a BibTeX file from the notes, and a
  two-layer faithfulness audit (mechanical substring check on evidence
  anchors plus a cold-context Claude subagent scoring prose fields against
  a published rubric) gates every note into the library. Version 0.17.0
  (2026-05-20) contains 244 curated notes — adds AMJ vol-66-no-3 (11
  notes: Bolino, Chatterjee, Ingram, Jones, Karp, Langley editorial,
  Lee, Maoret, Roccapriore, Toivonen, Watkins). Ingested under the
  complete three-gate prevention infrastructure (Step 0
  populate_manifest + Step 0.5 lint_manifests + Step 4.5
  verify_metadata); 11/11 Layer 1 first-try PASS and 11/11 Layer 2 PASS
  with a single PARTIAL verdict:
  77 from the Network for Business Sustainability (NBS) February 2026
  monthly digest (62 in v0.2.0 plus 15 previously-missing papers
  recovered in v0.3.0) and a 167-note Academy of Management Journal
  pilot across vol. 66 no. 3, vol. 66 no. 4, vol. 66 no. 5, vol. 66
  no. 6, vol. 67 no. 1, vol. 67 no. 2, vol. 67 no. 3, vol. 67 no. 4,
  vol. 67 no. 5, vol. 67 no. 6, vol. 68 no. 1 through vol. 68 no. 6,
  and vol. 69 no. 1 (vol. 66 no. 3 added in v0.17.0). The full library
  passes the v0.17.0 audit sweep with 244/244 PASS and zero CONTRADICTED
  verdicts across seventeen release cycles. An AGENTS.md file provides
  a tool-agnostic
  entry point so that AI agents (Claude Code, Cursor, Windsurf, custom
  SDK apps) can discover and consume the data with known faithfulness
  guarantees.
